com.interface21.jdbc.core
Class ReadOnlyResultSet

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.interface21.jdbc.core.ReadOnlyResultSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.sql.ResultSet
public class ReadOnlyResultSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.sql.ResultSet

A class that implements java.sql.ResultSet which is used in the JdbcTemplate class. This is the ResultSet instance which is passed as a parameter to the extract() callback method of the ManualExtractionSqlQueryWithParameters and ManualExtractionSqlQuery classes.

The objective is to be able to control that the user does not break the extraction mechanism by calling methods that disturb for instance the positioning of the cursor, such as next() or first(), or any other setter method. If such a call is made anyway, an InvalidDataAccessApiUsageException exception is thrown.

Overall, the class acts as a proxy to the actual ResultSet and filters out faulty calls to unauthorised methods behind the scenes. For that very reason, the wrapped methods are not documented here. Please refer to the official ResultSet Javadoc for more information.
